Tabaga (; , TabaÄŸa) is a rural locality (a selo) under the administrative jurisdiction of the city of republic significance of Yakutsk in the Sakha Republic, Russia. Its population as of the 2010 Census was 3360; down from 3746 recorded in the 2002 Census.
